Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.57,0:00:19.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The four-year-olds and under aren't here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.41,0:00:21.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.45,0:00:26.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What you said to me before,\NI thought about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.16,0:00:28.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.12,0:00:32.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's going smoothly for now.\NEveryone above five years old is on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.92,0:00:36.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They were surprised,\Nbut I think everything will be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.38,0:00:38.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our next training is under way too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.47,0:00:39.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.01,0:00:42.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do we do next? Should we tell them?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.93,0:00:44.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The kids four and under.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.43,0:00:47.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would they believe us?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.47,0:00:51.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And would they be able to hide it afterwards?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.02,0:00:52.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.52,0:00:55.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if we can really take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.11,0:01:00.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I don't believe in Norman's plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:06.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's a cliff, it's winter,\Nand Norman's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.91,0:01:10.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even after we get out,\Nthere'll be unpredictable situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.04,0:01:16.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's a little late to say this,\Nbut maybe Ray's thinking is also correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.55,0:01:17.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.59,0:01:21.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we take them with us,\Nwe can't let them get killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.63,0:01:23.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if we leave them here,\Nthey'll get shipped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.89,0:01:27.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know! I know that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.85,0:01:34.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even still, I can't leave them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.86,0:01:39.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray's right. Gilda's right, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.69,0:01:41.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.28,0:01:44.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want anyone\Nto get shipped out anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.99,0:01:48.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.62,0:01:50.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to take my whole family.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.54,0:01:53.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's escape with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.71,0:01:56.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.79,0:01:57.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.84,0:02:00.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well... um...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.80,0:02:03.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,what about the kids in the other plants?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.97,0:02:08.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it fine for only us to escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.22,0:02:11.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We've never seen them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.89,0:02:13.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,they're next door to us, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.06,0:02:16.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not knowing anything, just like us...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.52,0:02:18.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A family living happily...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.12,0:02:28.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, um, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.66,0:02:31.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do, Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.75,0:02:35.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.67,0:02:36.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.31,0:02:50.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you get Phil?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.52,0:02:53.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.60,0:02:55.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have something to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.27,0:02:57.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About the House and Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.03,0:03:02.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.65,0:03:03.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So it's just like I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:08.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:13.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When we were playing tag, I wondered\Nwhat Sister meant when she said "harvest".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.29,0:03:17.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She was looking through Ray's drawers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:22.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and Emma, when Norman left,\Nyou were really scared of Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.88,0:03:26.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I always thought it was weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.39,0:03:31.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.89,0:03:34.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Norman got harvested.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.06,0:03:38.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And Conny...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.48,0:03:41.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.69,0:03:43.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.32,0:03:47.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Phil.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.66,0:03:53.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't take them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.95,0:03:55.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only Phil knows the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.25,0:03:58.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The others don't know\Nabout the House or the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:01.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving that situation to Phil.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.67,0:04:05.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Phil, I need you to listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.59,0:04:07.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hesitating between two choices right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.72,0:04:11.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should I take everyone, including the babies?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.64,0:04:13.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or should I leave the kids\Nwho're under four years old?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.14,0:04:17.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We only get harvested\Nwhen we turn six years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.98,0:04:23.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even for Marnya, who has the earliest birthday,\Nwill have at least a year and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.77,0:04:26.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And 15 of the older kids will be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.61,0:04:31.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this House focuses on quality over quantity,\Nthen the pace of harvesting should go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.33,0:04:38.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In order to raise high-quality kids again, they can't\Nkill the younger ones who have potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.96,0:04:46.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On that point, the six kids who are four years old,\Nincluding you, have good scores.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.63,0:04:50.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At worst, I estimate\Nthat we have two years of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.84,0:04:53.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, do you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:55.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.22,0:04:57.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So leave us behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.19,0:05:02.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I haven't given up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.65,0:05:04.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll definitely return within two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.11,0:05:12.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I'll take Phil and the others,\Nas well as all the kids in the other four plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.49,0:05:15.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Phil, where are the other children?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.58,0:05:20.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:39.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.85,0:05:42.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Emma and everyone else?\NThey're not with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.98,0:05:44.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to get them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.56,0:05:45.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.52,0:05:47.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, make sure to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.41,0:05:58.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is 73584 from Plant Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.99,0:06:01.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The children have escaped! Sound the alarm!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:06.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It went off earlier than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.00,0:06:10.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do? We're still far from the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.51,0:06:13.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Attention all employees.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.30,0:06:15.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's an alert from Plant Three.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.14,0:06:18.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Following the fire in that plant,\N15 kids have escaped.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.26,0:06:20.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Two of the 15 are high-quality.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.22,0:06:23.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}From this point forward,\Nit will be dealt with maximum security.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.35,0:06:25.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can kill the others who aren't high-quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.19,0:06:29.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, don't damage any of their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.94,0:06:32.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Capture them immediately on sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.74,0:06:35.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do not let them get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.99,0:06:38.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Try and escape if you can...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.91,0:06:39.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.25,0:06:45.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll cross from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.96,0:06:48.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cross?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.25,0:06:51.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But at that time, Norman said...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.92,0:06:53.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we're escaping, it'll be through the bridge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.09,0:06:56.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But that's what anyone would think.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.34,0:06:59.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no way we'll cross the cliff.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.06,0:07:02.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's why we won't go to the bridge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.77,0:07:04.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll escape from the cliff.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.48,0:07:07.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I checked the distance to the other side\Nas well as the geographical features.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.15,0:07:10.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's dangerous,\Nbut there's a spot where you can cross.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.61,0:07:13.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And you have two months.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.82,0:07:15.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You have time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:22.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be okay. We trained a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.20,0:07:24.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trained?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.67,0:07:30.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- So close!\N- You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.19,0:07:56.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nat!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.07,0:07:56.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.29,0:08:06.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, are we really...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.33,0:08:07.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.83,0:08:10.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As long as the first person can cross...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.08,0:08:11.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.43,0:08:22.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.10,0:08:25.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we're up next!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.60,0:08:30.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ready...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:37.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.45,0:08:42.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:45.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See you later, Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:54.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:06.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You guys... when did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.85,0:09:09.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:23.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a smug face. How annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.07,0:09:27.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we were able to completely fool you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.49,0:09:30.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll show me something cool,\Nso shut up and come, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.29,0:09:33.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And isn't it cool?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.34,0:09:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.84,0:09:38.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a scenery we never thought we would see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.09,0:09:40.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.42,0:09:44.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it wouldn't be possible\Nto take everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.64,0:09:47.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they would be a hindrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.47,0:09:50.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hesitated too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.68,0:09:54.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, I made a decision,\Nand it's thanks to Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.44,0:09:58.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone joined with full faith\Nbecause it's Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.53,0:10:03.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's reckless and unreasonable,\Nbut she's honest,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:06.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and can say we're taking everyone\Nwithout a second thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.58,0:10:12.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to give up, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:19.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}- Did you find them?\N- No, keep looking!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.42,0:10:22.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those children haven't appeared\Nat the bridge yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.47,0:10:25.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not yet. Leave no stone unturned. Find them!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.68,0:10:26.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.18,0:10:28.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Could they be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.68,0:10:31.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just five more!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.94,0:10:35.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.02,0:10:41.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My hands... I'm sorry!\NWhen I think that there's a cliff below...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.32,0:10:46.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I start to think... What if I fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.74,0:10:47.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.59,0:11:07.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, Jemima.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:09.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's cross together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.81,0:11:10.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:11.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.06,0:11:14.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You still have the rope we used\Nto pull everyone up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.89,0:11:16.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.48,0:11:19.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tie Jemima to me using that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.61,0:11:22.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know how to go down?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.36,0:11:23.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I saw what everyone did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.61,0:11:25.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How about you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.99,0:11:28.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.28,0:11:32.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,W-We'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.08,0:11:33.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, super easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.29,0:11:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well said.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.00,0:11:38.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Jemima.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.94,0:11:59.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See? We got here, Jemima.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.62,0:12:12.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I lose, Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.80,0:12:26.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, you're the last one! Let's go, Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.66,0:13:00.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, House.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.59,0:13:07.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, our home that we loved so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.55,0:13:11.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye... Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.60,0:13:14.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go, Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.56,0:13:17.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My dear children...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.10,0:14:43.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isabella!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.06,0:14:46.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You scared me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.98,0:14:53.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I was climbing trees\Nand I heard a beautiful song, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.99,0:14:55.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you compose it, Leslie?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.74,0:14:57.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.66,0:15:00.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lovely melody.\NWhat's the name of the song?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.91,0:15:03.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't have a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.33,0:15:05.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing. Let me hear more of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.96,0:15:14.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's embarrassing,\Nso don't tell everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.26,0:15:15.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.53,0:17:48.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to put you in charge of Plant Three\Nstarting next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.95,0:17:51.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.40,0:18:23.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.87,0:18:27.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know that song?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.55,0:18:38.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.96,0:18:41.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you give birth to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:52.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Ray...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.56,0:18:56.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it was for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.94,0:18:58.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Longer than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:08.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess I've had enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.95,0:19:10.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.48,0:19:39.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.61,0:19:41.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.66,0:19:53.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I pray that you will find light.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.46,0:20:00.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.46,0:20:05.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. They escaped safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.14,0:20:15.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.60,0:20:20.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.40,0:20:23.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You must have been cold and lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.04,0:20:40.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We did it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.71,0:20:43.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We did it, Norman!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.05,0:20:49.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's the outside! We made it out!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.10,0:20:57.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll definitely come back to get everyone else.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.60,0:21:00.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Today we take the first step.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.96,0:21:19.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's our first morning.
